//! Cross-eye contradiction resolution engine.
//!
//! When two eyes disagree (e.g. Vision sees a button but DOM Reader
//! says it's not interactable), this engine applies the resolution
//! hierarchy to produce a consistent view.
//!
//! Resolution hierarchy (highest authority wins):
//! 1. DOM Reader (ground truth for element state)
//! 2. Page Diff (ground truth for what changed)
//! 3. Goal Verifier (ground truth for goal progress)
//! 4. Vision Model (best guess, overridable)
//! 5. Error Detector (only consulted on failure)

/// Resolves cross-eye contradictions and returns a unified perception.
pub struct ContradictionResolver;
